speech.p: I am aware of the hon. Gentleman’s concerns, which he is going to talk through tomorrow with the Under-Secretary of State for Transport, my hon. Friend the Member for Lewes (Norman Baker). I assure him that no final decisions have been made. I emphasise that the HLOS investment that we are making will open up real opportunities for us to cascade rolling stock. For example, the high-speed diesel fleet that is currently on the midland main line—the Meridian stock—will be available, and we will see how we can use that effectively on other parts of the network.
